Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<prome@promedmail.org>

[The number of cases and deaths in the current listeriosis outbreak traced to rockmelons (cantaloupes) in Australia have increased to 17 and 4, respectively.

State health departments were able to pinpoint the source of the outbreak to a farm in Nericon, near the city of Griffith, in the New South Wales (NSW), Riverina district (http://theconversation.com/what-is-listeria-and-how-does-it-spread-in-rockmelons-92651). However, we have not been told so far how the rockmelons became contaminated.

Riverina is an agricultural region of south western NSW, Australia. A map of Australia showing the location of Nericon can be found at https://www.whereis.com/nsw/nericon-2680. A HealthMap of New South Wales, Australia can be found at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5672344,284.

My colleague, ProMED-mail moderator LXL reports that Qatar has now banned the importation of melons from Australia and New Zealand (source article in Chinese, machine translated, http://spzx.foods1.com/show_2726017.htm). - Mod.ML]
